==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deceivableness
<hw>De*ceiv"a*ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capability
of deceiving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With all <qex>deceivableness</qex> of unrighteousness.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Thess. ii. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Liability to be deceived or misled; <as>as, the
<ex>deceivableness</ex> of a child</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deceivably</ent>⟦br⟧
